SIMPLE: malevolent
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Malevolent
<hw>Ma*lev"o*lent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>malevolens</ets>, <ets>-entis</ets>; <ets>male</ets> ill +
<ets>volens</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>velle</ets> to be willing or disposed,
to wish. See <er>Malice</er>, and <er>Voluntary</er>.]</ety>
<def>Wishing evil; disposed to injure others; rejoicing in another's
misfortune.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Ill-disposed; envious; mischievous; evil-minded;
spiteful; malicious; malignant; rancorous.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Malevolently</ent>⟦br⟧
